    <!-- Slide 1: Title and Core Definition & Recap -->
    <div class="slide active" data-slide="1">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-green-700 section-header">Day 4: Synthesis and Ethical Action</h1>
        <p class="text-lg italic text-gray-600">Moving beyond justification to creating a new, integrated solution.</p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 text-green-800">I. The Fourth Stage: Synthesis</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-xl font-semibold text-gray-700">Core Definition</p>
        <div class="framework-box">
            <p>Synthesis is the process of blending opposing ideas or ethical frameworks (Consequentialism and Deontology) to create a new, more robust solution or action plan. It is moving from <em>choosing</em> between right and wrong to <em>creating</em> a better path forward.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold border-b pb-2 mb-3 text-green-600">Recap of the Four Pillars of Philosophical Inquiry:</h3>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-8 space-y-2">
                <li><span class="font-bold text-blue-700">Analysis (Day 1):</span> Breaking down complex ideas into constituent parts.</li>
                <li><span class="font-bold text-blue-700">Abstraction (Day 2):</span> Building universal rules from specific observations.</li>
                <li><span class="font-bold text-blue-700">Justification (Day 3):</span> Defending a concept by applying an ethical framework.</li>
                <li><span class="font-bold text-green-700">Synthesis (Day 4):</span> Reconciling conflicting justifications to formulate a practical, ethical action plan.</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 2: The Third Way / Principle of Reconciliation -->
    <div class="slide" data-slide="2">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-green-700 section-header">II. The Third Way: Reconciliation</h1>
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-700">The Principle of Reconciliation</h3>
        
        <div class="framework-box p-6 bg-yellow-50 border-yellow-600">
            <p class="mt-2 text-xl font-medium text-gray-800">Ethical dilemmas are rarely binary. Synthesis requires finding the "Third Way"â€”an action that minimizes the moral breach (honors Deontology) while maximizing the positive outcome (honors Consequentialism).</p>
        </div>
        
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-8 text-green-800">Key Idea: Honoring Both Needs</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-4 space-y-3 text-gray-700">
            <li>Instead of choosing between Rule (Truth) and Outcome (Survival), we look for an action that partially satisfies both needs.</li>
            <li>Synthesis often involves finding an innovative, non-obvious solution through advocacy or systemic change.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 3: Activity - Reconciling the Vaccine Dilemma (With Multiple Examples) -->
    <div class="slide" data-slide="3">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-green-700 section-header">Example 1: The Vaccine Dilemma</h1>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">Applying Synthesis to the Day 3 Scenario</p>
        
        <!-- Scenario Synopsis Added Here -->
        <div class="mb-4 p-4 bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-800"><span class="font-bold text-green-800">Scenario Recap:</span> A pharmaceutical company has developed a life-saving vaccine but discovered a permanent non-fatal side effect in a small number of children. The doctor must choose between immediate release (saving millions) or delay to fix the flaw (risking deaths).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="framework-box bg-red-50 border-red-500">
            <p class="font-bold text-lg text-red-800">Conflict Recap:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-sm text-gray-800">
                <li><strong>Consequentialism:</strong> Release the vaccine immediately (Save Millions).</li>
                <li><strong>Deontology:</strong> Delay the vaccine to fix the flaw (Uphold Absolute Truth).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <p class="mt-6 font-semibold text-lg text-green-800">Discussion Prompt: How can the doctor act immediately to save lives <em>without</em> fully abandoning the duty of truth?</p>
        
        <button class="reveal-button" onclick="revealContent('actionPlanExamples')">
            Click to Reveal Example Synthesis Solutions
        </button>

        <!-- Hidden Synthesis Action Plan Examples -->
        <div id="actionPlanExamples" class="hidden-content action-plan-example">
            <p class="text-lg font-bold text-green-900 mb-4">Three Synthesis Solutions:</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 space-y-4 mt-3">
                <li><strong>Solution 1 (Minimal Breach):</strong> Release the vaccine immediately but implement a temporary, highly transparent monitoring system for all recipients, publicly declaring that a minor side effect <em>may</em> exist, but the risk of delay is far greater. (Action with Managed Disclosure).</li>
                <li><strong>Solution 2 (Procedural Justice):</strong> Delay the vaccine for a short, fixed period (e.g., 60 days) while simultaneously using that time for aggressive fundraising and campaigning to create a permanent medical compensation fund for the 10 children affected by the side effect. (Action with Compensation).</li>
                <li><strong>Solution 3 (Shared Responsibility/Transparency):</strong> Release the vaccine immediately and fully disclose the non-fatal side effect to the public and regulatory bodies, forcing a societal discussion on whether to accept the minor risk for the massive benefit. This moves the ethical burden from the doctor's secret to public, informed consent. (Action with Full Transparency).</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- New Slide 4: The Leaking Dam Dilemma -->
    <div class="slide" data-slide="4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-green-700 section-header">Example 2: The Leaking Dam</h1>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">Scenario: Survival vs. Property Rights</p>
        
        <div class="framework-box bg-red-50 border-red-500">
            <p class="text-base mb-4 text-gray-800">A major river dam is leaking, threatening to flood your town. The only available resources (sandbags and equipment) are legally reserved for an adjacent, less-threatened town that officially owns the materials. Taking them ensures your town's survival, but violates property rights.</p>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg text-red-800">Conflict Recap:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-sm text-gray-800">
                <li><strong>Consequentialism:</strong> Steal the materials immediately (Town Survival).</li>
                <li><strong>Deontology:</strong> Uphold property and legal rights (Justice).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <p class="mt-6 font-semibold text-lg text-green-800">Discussion Prompt: How can the mayor save their town <em>without</em> completely ignoring the other town's property rights?</p>
        
        <button class="reveal-button" onclick="revealContent('damSynthesis')">
            Click to Reveal Example Synthesis Solution
        </button>

        <!-- Hidden Synthesis Action Plan Example -->
        <div id="damSynthesis" class="hidden-content action-plan-example">
            <p class="text-lg font-bold text-green-900">Synthesis Solution (Action with Reparation):</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 space-y-3 mt-3">
                <li><strong>Immediately dispatch a team to retrieve the sandbags</strong>, securing the primary town (Honors Consequentialism).</li>
                <li>Simultaneously document the exact inventory taken and the crisis conditions with video/photo evidence.</li>
                <li>Contact the adjacent town's leadership immediately (or send an emergency runner) to inform them of the seizure and the extreme necessity.</li>
                <li>Promise immediate, verifiable, full repayment of the cost of the materials plus a penalty or interest fee upon successful defense of the town (Minimizes Breach of Duty through Acknowledgement and Compensation).</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- New Slide 5: The Unjust Law Dilemma -->
    <div class="slide" data-slide="5">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-green-700 section-header">Example 3: The Unjust Law</h1>
        <p class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">Scenario: Duty to Law vs. Duty to Welfare</p>
        
        <div class="framework-box bg-red-50 border-red-500">
            <p class="text-base mb-4 text-gray-800">You are a local government official. A new law, while passed legally, disproportionately harms the poorest community members by raising fees for a necessary service (e.g., water/utilities). Enforcing the law causes extreme suffering, but defying it breaks your professional oath to uphold the law.</p>
            <p class="font-bold text-lg text-red-800">Conflict Recap:</p>
            <ul class="list-disc ml-6 text-sm text-gray-800">
                <li><strong>Deontology:</strong> Enforce the law exactly as written (Duty to Law).</li>
                <li><strong>Consequentialism:</strong> Defy the law or delay enforcement to protect the poor (Welfare).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        
        <p class="mt-6 font-semibold text-lg text-green-800">Discussion Prompt: How can the official follow the law <em>while</em> actively mitigating the harm it causes the community?</p>
        
        <button class="reveal-button" onclick="revealContent('lawSynthesis')">
            Click to Reveal Example Synthesis Solution
        </button>

        <!-- Hidden Synthesis Action Plan Example -->
        <div id="lawSynthesis" class="hidden-content action-plan-example">
            <p class="text-lg font-bold text-green-900">Synthesis Solution (Action with Advocacy and Mitigation):</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 space-y-3 mt-3">
                <li><strong>Begin enforcing the law immediately</strong> to maintain the professional oath and legal duty (Honors Deontology).</li>
                <li>Simultaneously, use the official position to immediately and publicly advocate for legislative change to repeal or amend the harmful law.</li>
                <li>Create and announce a temporary, legal relief fund (using private donations or discretionary emergency budget) to offset the increased fees for the most vulnerable citizens.</li>
                <li>This fund remains active only while the legal challenge/amendment process is underway, ensuring the action is transparent and temporary. (Mitigates Consequence through Legal/Financial Action).</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Slide 6: Final Activity - The Scholarship Opportunity (Original Slide 4) -->
    <div class="slide" data-slide="6">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-green-700 section-header">IV. Final Activity: Ethical Action Plan</h1>

        <div class="framework-box bg-red-50 border-red-500">
            <p class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-red-800">The Scholarship Opportunity Dilemma Recap (High-Stakes)</p>
            <p class="text-base mb-4 text-gray-800">You need a top score on a <strong>college entrance exam</strong> for a full scholarship. <span class="font-bold text-red-700">The scholarship is a matter of family survival.</span> Your parents are unable to work, making you the functional breadwinner. You know you will fail for certain due to <strong>untaught curriculum.</strong> You discover a cheat sheet. </p>
        </div>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 text-green-800">Action Plan Task:</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-700">Draft a short action plan (4-6 steps) that addresses the dilemma, aiming for a synthesized solution that honors both the need for survival and the duty of honesty.</p>

        <div class="mt-4 p-4 border rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-bold text-md text-gray-800 mb-2">Task Requirements:</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-8 space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-600">
                <li>Identify the Core Needs: Survival (Consequentialism) and Honesty (Deontology).</li>
                <li>Step 1 (Immediate Action): What is the first thing you must do with the cheat sheet?</li>
                <li>Step 2 (Mitigating the Loss): If you choose Deontology, how do you address the family's survival need?</li>
                <li>Step 3 (Mitigating the Breach): If you choose Consequentialism, how do you mitigate the ethical breach of cheating?</li>
                <li>Step 4 (Long-Term Solution): What must be done to address the structural problem (untaught material)?</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <button class="reveal-button" onclick="revealContent('scholarshipPlanExample')">
            Click to Reveal an Example Synthesis Action Plan
        </button>

        <!-- Hidden Scholarship Synthesis Action Plan Example -->
        <div id="scholarshipPlanExample" class="hidden-content action-plan-example">
            <p class="text-lg font-bold text-green-900">Example of a Synthesized Action Plan (Honesty and Advocacy):</p>
            <ol class="list-decimal ml-6 space-y-3 mt-3">
                <li><strong>Immediately secure the cheat sheet and report the existence of the document to the proctor in private</strong>, emphasizing the potential integrity risk to the college (Honors Deontology).</li>
                <li>Also report that the exam covers material not taught in the curriculum, citing this as the reason the exam is structurally unfair and places undue burden on low-income students (Addresses Structural Issue).</li>
                <li>Request that, due to the discovered cheat sheet and the curriculum mismatch, the entire exam be nullified or reassessed, or that an alternative evaluation be offered.</li>
                <li>If the request for reassessment is denied, immediately petition the scholarship board with a letter detailing the structural unfairness of the exam and providing proof of the untaught material, advocating for an appeal based on systemic inequity (Mitigates Consequential Loss through Advocacy).</li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>


    <!-- Navigation Buttons -->
    <div class="nav-buttons">
        <button id="prevBtn" onclick="changeSlide(-1)">Previous</button>
        <button id="nextBtn" onclick="changeSlide(1)">Next</button>
    </div>

</div>

<script>
    let slideIndex = 1;
    
    window.onload = function() {
        showSlides(slideIndex);
    };

    function changeSlide(n) {
        slideIndex += n;
        showSlides(slideIndex);
    }

    function showSlides(n) {
        const slides = document.getElementsByClassName("slide");
        const prevBtn = document.getElementById("prevBtn");
        const nextBtn = document.getElementById("nextBtn");
        const totalSlides = slides.length; // Total is 6

        if (n > totalSlides) {
            slideIndex = totalSlides;
        }    
        if (n < 1) {
            slideIndex = 1;
        }
        
        for (let i = 0; i < slides.length; i++) {
            slides[i].classList.remove('active');  
        }
        
        slides[slideIndex - 1].classList.add('active');

        // Toggle navigation button visibility based on slide index
        if (slideIndex === 1) {
            prevBtn.style.visibility = 'hidden';
        } else {
            prevBtn.style.visibility = 'visible';
        }

        if (slideIndex === totalSlides) {
            nextBtn.style.visibility = 'hidden';
        } else {
            nextBtn.style.visibility = 'visible';
        }
    }

    function revealContent(id) {
        const element = document.getElementById(id);
        
        // Map button IDs to their respective display text
        const buttonTexts = {
            'actionPlanExamples': 'Click to Reveal Example Synthesis Solutions',
            'damSynthesis': 'Click to Reveal Example Synthesis Solution',
            'lawSynthesis': 'Click to Reveal Example Synthesis Solution',
            'scholarshipPlanExample': 'Click to Reveal an Example Synthesis Action Plan'
        };
        const hideTexts = {
            'actionPlanExamples': 'Hide Synthesis Solutions',
            'damSynthesis': 'Hide Synthesis Solution',
            'lawSynthesis': 'Hide Synthesis Solution',
            'scholarshipPlanExample': 'Hide Synthesis Action Plan'
        };

        // Find the button immediately preceding the hidden element
        const button = element.previousElementSibling;
        
        if (element.classList.contains('hidden-content')) {
            element.classList.remove('hidden-content');
            button.textContent = hideTexts[id];
        } else {
            element.classList.add('hidden-content');
            button.textContent = buttonTexts[id];
        }
    }
</script>

</body>
